Δ
𝑛
𝐿
≤
0
Triadic Metric: Its expected value behaves like a supermartingale — monotone in expectation — ensuring instability doesn’t grow.

Containment: Monotonic shrinkage of 
𝜃
𝑡
 or bounded curvature accumulation are monotonicity conditions that certify lawful coherence.

